title: Grateful Dead Live at Providence Civic Center on 1984-04-27
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave (24 bit) > TLH > FLAC 2448 tagged. Transfer by Andrew F. 07/2013
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, Dire Wolf, Minglewood Blues, Row Jimmy, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Althea, My Brother Esau, Big Railroad Blues-> The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Playin' In The Band-> China Doll-> High Time-> Women Are Smarter-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: Touch Of Gray

reviews.review_text: Playing in the Band Very nice audience recording. Playing in the Band (PITB) is tight, very fluid, nothing to do but smile, smile, smile. 1984 begins with relatively short PITBs with this one clocking in a little over 10 minutes.  Still a very full expression of the song's possibilities. Beginning in '83, China Doll or Crazy Fingers became the preferred segue for Jerry. This night continues that pattern.
